+# CGO Test Files Consolidation - Complete
+
+## Summary
+
+Successfully consolidated misc/cgo/test files to reduce compilation overhead as per issue #26473.
+
+## Changes Made
+
+### File Consolidation
+- **Before**: 118 .go files (111 test files + 7 coordinator files)
+- **After**: 17 .go files (11 consolidated test files + 6 coordinator files)
+- **Reduction**: 101 files removed (85.6% reduction in test files)
+
+### New Consolidated Files Created
+
+1. **test.go** (37KB, 1,885 lines)
+   - Consolidates 76 generic files WITHOUT `//export` directives
+   - Includes: align.go, api.go, basic.go, and 73 issue files
+
+2. **testx.go** (121KB, 2,295 lines)
+   - Consolidates 17 generic files WITH `//export` directives
+   - Includes: callback.go, cthread.go, exports.go, and 14 issue files with exports
+
+3. **test_unix.go** (9.7KB, 549 lines)
+   - Build tag: `// +build !windows`
+   - Consolidates 11 Unix-specific files WITHOUT `//export` directives
+
+4. **testx_unix.go** (2.8KB, 148 lines)
+   - Build tag: `// +build !windows`
+   - Consolidates 3 Unix-specific files WITH `//export` directives
+
+5. **test_windows.go** (457 bytes, 30 lines)
+   - Build tag: `// +build windows`
+   - Consolidates 4 Windows-specific stub functions
+
+6. **testx_windows.go** (1.1KB, 50 lines)
+   - Build tag: `// +build windows`
+   - Consolidates 1 Windows-specific file WITH `//export` directives
+
+7. **test_darwin.go** (1.5KB, 62 lines)
+   - Build tag: `// +build darwin,cgo,!internal,!race`
+   - Darwin-specific CoreFoundation tests from issue21897
+
+8. **test_notdarwin.go** (338 bytes, 15 lines)
+   - Build tag: `// +build !darwin`
+   - Stub for issue21897 on non-Darwin platforms
+
+9. **test_linux_amd64.go** (1.4KB, 55 lines)
+   - Build tag: `// +build amd64,linux`
+   - Linux amd64-specific tests from issue24206
+
+10. **test_generic.go** (332 bytes, 16 lines)
+    - Build tag: `// +build !amd64 !linux`
+    - Stub for issue24206 on non-amd64/linux platforms
+
+11. **testx_gccgo.go** (303 bytes, 18 lines)
+    - Build tag: `// +build gccgo`
+    - gccgo-specific tests from issue8945
+
+### Files Preserved
+- cgo_test.go (test wrapper functions)
+- cgo_linux_test.go, cgo_unix_test.go, cgo_stubs_android_test.go
+- overlaydir_test.go, pkg_test.go
+- All .c files (19 files) - referenced by consolidated .go files
+
+### Key Improvements
+
+1. **Single import "C" per main file**: Reduces cgo invocations from 111 to 11
+2. **Organized by issue number**: Easy to locate tests
+3. **Proper platform separation**: Unix/Windows/Darwin/Linux-specific code properly isolated
+4. **Export/non-export separation**: test.go (no exports) vs testx.go (with exports)
+5. **Compilation verified**: `go test -c` succeeds, generates 4.7MB test binary
+
+## Expected Performance Impact
+
+- **go test -c** time: Expected to drop from 20s to under 5s (75% improvement)
+- **all.bash** savings: Removes ~23.4r 29.0u 21.5s 
+- **Build multiplier**: Test built 4 times in all.bash with different settings, multiplying savings
+
+## Structure
+
+Each consolidated file follows this pattern:
+```go
+// Copyright header
+// Build tags (if platform-specific)
+
+package cgotest
+
+/*
+// From file1.go
+<C preamble from file1>
+
+// From file2.go
+<C preamble from file2>
+...
+*/
+import "C"
+
+import (
+    // Consolidated imports
+)
+
+// file1.go
+<Go code from file1>
+
+// file2.go  
+<Go code from file2>
+...
+```
+
+## Technical Details
+
+- **Duplicate C types removed**: xxpthread_mutex_t, struct definitions
+- **Enum naming conflicts resolved**: Added unique suffixes where needed
+- **Platform guards added**: #ifdef __APPLE__ for CoreFoundation
+- **Multiple definition errors fixed**: Made C variables extern or static
+- **Import "C" statements merged**: All C code in single block per file
+- **Build tags correctly applied**: Ensures proper platform-specific compilation
+
+## Testing
+
+All tests compile successfully:
+```bash
+$ go test -c -o /tmp/cgotest
+$ ls -lh /tmp/cgotest
+-rwxrwxr-x 1 agent_user agent_user 4.7M Jan 18 12:25 /tmp/cgotest
+```
+
+## For Issue #26473
+
+This consolidation addresses the issue raised in golang/go#26473 regarding excessive
+cgo compilation overhead in misc/cgo/test. The reduction from 111 to 11 files with
+import "C" statements directly reduces cgo invocations by 90%, significantly
+improving build times.
