+CGO TEST FILE CONSOLIDATION SUMMARY
+================================================================================
+
+Date: 2026-01-18
+Task: Consolidated 111 individual Go test files into 6 organized files
+
+================================================================================
+CONSOLIDATED FILES CREATED
+================================================================================
+
+1. test.go (38K, 2066 lines)
+   - 72 generic files WITHOUT //export directives
+   - No platform-specific build tags
+   - Sorted: non-issue files alphabetically, then by issue number
+
+2. testx.go (122K, 2323 lines)
+   - 17 generic files WITH //export directives
+   - No platform-specific build tags
+   - Sorted: non-issue files alphabetically, then by issue number
+
+3. test_unix.go (13K, 626 lines)
+   - 14 Unix-specific files WITHOUT //export directives
+   - Build tag: // +build !windows
+   - Includes files with _linux, _unix, _darwin suffixes
+   - Includes files with darwin/linux/unix build tags
+
+4. testx_unix.go (2.8K, 151 lines)
+   - 3 Unix-specific files WITH //export directives
+   - Build tag: // +build !windows
+   - Files: cgo_thread_lock.go, issue4029.go, sigprocmask.go
+
+5. test_windows.go (461 bytes, 38 lines)
+   - 4 Windows-specific files WITHOUT //export directives
+   - Build tag: // +build windows
+   - Files: issue3250w.go, issue3729w.go, issue4029w.go, issue5337w.go
+
+6. testx_windows.go (1.1K, 51 lines)
+   - 1 Windows-specific file WITH //export directives
+   - Build tag: // +build windows
+   - Files: issue8517_windows.go
+
+================================================================================
+CONSOLIDATION RULES APPLIED
+================================================================================
+
+1. File Organization:
+   - Files sorted within each category: non-issue files alphabetically first,
+     then issue files by issue number
+   - Each file section marked with "// filename.go" comment
+
+2. C Preamble Handling:
+   - Files with /* */ style C comments: consolidated into single /* */ block
+   - Files with // style C comments: preserved as // comments with separate
+     import "C" statements
+   - Each C preamble marked with "// From filename.go" comment
+
+3. Import Consolidation:
+   - All Go imports deduplicated and merged into single import block
+   - Standalone import statements removed from code sections
+   - Both "unsafe" and _ "unsafe" preserved (different purposes)
+
+4. Platform Detection:
+   - Filename patterns: _linux.go, _unix.go, _darwin.go, _windows.go
+   - Build tags: // +build with platform constraints
+   - Files with darwin/linux/unix tags → test_unix.go or testx_unix.go
+   - Files with windows tags → test_windows.go or testx_windows.go
+
+5. Export Detection:
+   - Files containing //export directives → testx*.go files
+   - Files without //export directives → test*.go files
+
+================================================================================
+FILES EXCLUDED FROM CONSOLIDATION
+================================================================================
+
+The following files were NOT consolidated (remain as separate files):
+- *_test.go files (test files with special test framework requirements)
+- cgo_test.go (main test runner)
+- cgo_*_test.go (platform-specific test runners)
+- overlaydir_test.go (test infrastructure)
+- pkg_test.go (test infrastructure)
+
+These files reference the consolidated test files and drive the test execution.
+
+================================================================================
+STRUCTURE OF CONSOLIDATED FILES
+================================================================================
+
+Each consolidated file follows this format:
+
+```go
+// Copyright 2011 The Go Authors. All rights reserved.
+// Use of this source code is governed by a BSD-style
+// license that can be found in the LICENSE file.
+
+// +build <constraint if needed>
+
+package cgotest
+
+/*
+// From file1.go
+<C preamble from file1.go>
+
+// From file2.go
+<C preamble from file2.go>
+
+... etc for all files with /* */ C preambles
+*/
+import "C"
+
+// From file3.go (files with // C comments)
+// C preamble line 1
+// C preamble line 2
+import "C"
+
+import (
+    <all unique imports from all files, sorted>
+)
+
+// file1.go
+
+<All Go code from file1.go>
+
+// file2.go
+
+<All Go code from file2.go>
+
+... etc for all files
+```
+
+================================================================================
+VERIFICATION
+================================================================================
+
+File sizes and line counts:
+- test.go:           38K,  2066 lines (72 files)
+- testx.go:         122K,  2323 lines (17 files)
+- test_unix.go:      13K,   626 lines (14 files)
+- testx_unix.go:    2.8K,   151 lines (3 files)
+- test_windows.go:   461B,   38 lines (4 files)
+- testx_windows.go: 1.1K,    51 lines (1 file)
+TOTAL:              177K,  5255 lines (111 files)
+
+Key features verified:
+✓ All C preambles properly consolidated
+✓ Import statements deduplicated
+✓ Standalone import statements removed from code sections
+✓ Build tags correctly applied
+✓ Files sorted by issue number
+✓ Both /* */ and // C comment styles preserved appropriately
+✓ //export directives preserved in code sections
+
+================================================================================
